WF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMGQxN2U2OTUtNjVkYi00Yzc4LWFkYTctMjc0MjQ4OGQ5MDA0XzE3MTh4MTQ0OC5wbmc= 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/k- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>Installing the inside-out globe for the 1942 exhibit “Airways to Peace,” <a href="https://www.moma.org/calendar/exhibitions/3138" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">MoMA: 1943</a></figcaption></figure><p>By 1946, Bayer was in Aspen, helping lay the groundwork for the Aspen Institute for Humanistic Studies. Yes, <em>that </em>Aspen Institute.</p><p>From there, Bayer embarked on his <em>World Geo-Graphic Atlas</em>. It is a grand tour of America, the world, and the universe employing cartographic, graphic statistic, and printing design sophistication gained over the prior decades.</p><p>The book showcased immense ambitions. It was financed by the Container Corporation of America to the tune of $400,000—which would be a lot of money <em>today </em>for a book project. (That’s about $5 million in today’s dollars.)</p><p>To me, Bayer’s <em>Atlas</em> is the punctuation on over a century of progress in popular information design that began with 19th century student pictorial encyclopedias, extended through national statistical atlases, and crested with the Isotype Institute’s publications.</p><p>An opening choice detail from the book’s contents—a map explaining the circuitous order of its pages of U.S. states with a snaking red line—reveals the quirky attention given to its finest details.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0187a323-8cbc-4e64-ae35-2c5be059794b_1536x1097.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/sRG1mxCUVo40m2ok0_LKGfF-U3- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/GpghxtL9Y9tc9H_4MUQVL3pDzyEbKd_xXwISPYVVbGo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYwMTg3YTMyMy04Y2JjLTRlNjQtYWUzNS0yYzViZTA1OTc5NGJfMTUzNngxMDk3LmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/UNp86BgPeWfBfVANNMjshd- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-7RcEZE596OCzbwEwlxkuXTFnhuDYwc5gmWZwf-CyHA=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18yNDAwLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMDE4N2EzMjMtOGNiYy00ZTY0LWFlMzUtMmM1YmUwNTk3OTRiXzE1MzZ4MTA5Ny5qcGVn" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/VIXxYZwFR_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Ma_FA4bHCl5slRgoQJ4xGDWcx_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/YnncD_O-569B2xGorNLK9PyY6I-Wlqb_-LuCwPrqWjA=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMDE4N2EzMjMtOGNiYy00ZTY0LWFlMzUtMmM1YmUwNTk3OTRiXzE1MzZ4MTA5Ny5qcGVn 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/bFsmZ70jkn2s3wNa_v94IAjbg51nCD3Z-gkwgXQ8p7M=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMDE4N2EzMjMtOGNiYy00ZTY0LWFlMzUtMmM1YmUwNTk3OTRiXzE1MzZ4MTA5Ny5qcGVn 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p>You can see the original Atlas in beautiful detail at the <a href="https://www.davidrumsey.com/luna/servlet/s/2ex67c" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">David Rumsey Map Collection</a>.</p><h4>Mythology</h4><p>Benjamin Benus’s new book reveals loads of behind-the-scenes about the conception, production, and reception of Herbert Bayer’s <em>Atlas</em>. It is boasts delicious reproductions of the atlas’s pages.</p><p>I particularly appreciate how Benus shows how Bayer referenced his own work. For example, compare how this big red dot compositions from 1926 . . . </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ec6c39f-df93-4ecf-8f65-68432accdbbc_1024x731.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/LqQh4RoFJfl_5FqlhEgKZqkLUzmM5_nGShiCaukJmxA=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY3ZWM2YzM5Zi1kZjkzLTRlY2YtOGY2NS02ODQzMmFjY2RiYmNfMTAyNHg3MzEuanBlZw== 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Ug66GNLts3tnchFwBvrYpT6EU3vXBDI-G0X9Iroon-I=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY3ZWM2YzM5Zi1kZjkzLTRlY2YtOGY2NS02ODQzMmFjY2RiYmNfMTAyNHg3MzEuanBlZw== 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/dIhG_XbKk2QF8QW8Z38pl79z- 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Q5alkhwInAnh-tvDeyt8mJ- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/sF2JpRCB-vf5TzaEEC-" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ditrPsnftXsQSMm69g0YFyDt1F- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/g_1Yau8QuGFvUFw53Ao4g9fuNG- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/mb3hJAYEp_id4YI8APnOQeF8Tx8FC5GlM_fbDeV65qg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNB